cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper describes the use of a video camera and convolutional neural networks for fruit and vegetable identification. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the retraining of neural networks for object classification. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the system uses machine learning techniques for automated identification. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper discusses the usability of the graphical user interface and a heuristic evaluation was performed with users. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is less likely but still possible as the system involves retrieving information (i.e. price) based on the identified fruit or vegetable.
